content: Kay, so, apparently, in my previous review, I asked for a K function. What I didn't know was that this freaking calculator can do f of x functions, or f(x)= yadda yadda. I wish there was something to tell me, or I'm flippin' blind!
replyContent:
Have you tried defining a function? You can write f(x)=15*x, and then can ask for f(5), f(10), etc.

Hope that helps!

content: This is a poor calculator. You can not divide. If I want to divide 8 √∑ 2 it will change it to 8/2 in fraction form, every time. There is a separate button a/b to turn your numbers into fractions. Why make the divide button only turn numbers into fractions of there's already another button for that function, instead of it actually dividing? Like it should.
replyContent:
Thanks for the feedback, Lindsey! I'm confused about the concern: it does indeed divide 8 by 2, returning a value of 4. It just displays it as 8/2 instead of as 8√∑2. The main motivation there was to avoid ambiguity that comes from things like 8√∑2(3+1), ambiguity which isn't present when rendering as a fraction. 

Hope that helps!
